oor Extension Cord (25ft)\tHeavy-duty, outdoor-rated\t~$30\tHome Depot Reflectix Insulation (24\" × 10ft)\tWrap around tub for heat retention\t~$18\tHome Depot Bungee Cords (4-pack)\tSecure insulation\t~$8\tHome Depot TOTAL: ~$185–$210 PERFORMANCE COMPARISON Configuration\tCollapsible?\tWeight\tFolded Size\tMax Temp\tMelt Rate\tSetup Time Prototype H: Silicone Tub\t✅ Yes\t~8 lbs\t20\" × 20\" × 4\" flat\t160–180°F\t~35–45 lbs/hr\t3 min Prototype G: Metal Can\t❌ No\t~15 lbs\t21\" × 30\" (as-is)\t180–200°F\t~50 lbs/hr\t5 min WHY LIMIT TO 1500W (NOT 1800W) FOR SILICONE? Factor\tReasoning Heat distribution\tSilicone walls don't conduct heat; localized hot spots near element Material safety margin\tKeep water at ~160–170°F to stay well below silicone's 392°F limit Structural integrity\tSilicone softens slightly at high temps; 1500W maintains rigidity Circuit safety\t1500W = 12.5A, safer continuous load on 15A circuit 5-STEP SETUP (COLLAPSIBLE VERSION) Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                    COLLAPSIBLE SNOW MELTER                  │ │                     SETUP WORKFLOW                          │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │                                                             │ │  STEP 1: UNFOLD                                             │ │  ┌──────────┐                                               │ │  │ ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ │  Pop open silicone tub                       │ │  │ ▓      ▓ │  Place on flat concrete/asphalt               │ │  │ ▓      ▓ │                                               │ │  └──────────┘                                               │ │       ↓                                                     │ │  STEP 2: INSULATE                                           │ │  ┌──────────┐                                               │ │  │ ░░░░░░░░ │  Wrap Reflectix around outside                │ │  │ ░▓▓▓▓▓▓░ │  Secure with bungee cords                     │ │  │ ░▓    ▓